snippet.textDisplay: It's very simple. In order to have a "warranty" the company that manufactures the brake must use consistent parts. The brake fluid is part of this equation. Baby oil/Mineral oil can vary measurably from brand to brand. Hence, it can NOT be "recommended" in cases where warranty is an issue. That being said... I've raced the hell out of Johnson's and it works fine. But... just like changing pad and rotor material, the viscosity (thickness) of the oil will have an effect. If you are fighting for 10th's of a second, it will make a difference. If you are low on funds or want to save a trip, it is 100% legit. It has never failed any of my Magura brakes. And yes, I actually do spend the extra few cents to get a quality name brand "baby oil."

snippet.textDisplay:
Hi Seth, well I worked for some Brake manufacturers in the past and was involved in the R&D of some Nixe products over the years. Most mineral oil brakes use the same materials for their seals, Membran or even the piston, so you can run all sorts of mineral oil without demaging the brakes.
Clearly the boiling temperature is the most important difference between cheap oils and some racing oils used by their teams or in WRX (Not in the brakes but the gear boxes). So yes Baby oil will Do the Job for 95% of the riders. Legal notice every Brand has to narrow down some options to denie warranties... (only use Brand x oil) otherwise it would be imposibile to garanty their function.
You may Do a simple boiling test to See the Main difference between them.

snippet.textDisplay:
Seth, Baby Oil is essentially Mineral Oil, which is Liquidum Paraffinum. Liquid Paraffine Oil. The most harmless substance for seal rings, skin and baby butt. Hydrogenated Paraffine Oil (binding hydrogen atoms) turns into paraffine wax, which is essentially Vaseline. Vaseline can be used on all rubber seal rings without any hesitation.
I assume that Shimano/Magura Oil is nothing else than common colored Mineral Oil, without perfume. I once asked Magura for advice since my Magura "Royal Blood" (the blue oil) was empty and if I could use Shimano Oil (the red oil). They answered yes. So it's all the same.
